<item>
            <title>[SPARK-4253] Ignore spark.driver.host in yarn-cluster and standalone-cluster mode</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-4253</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We actually don&apos;t know where driver will be before it is launched in yarn-cluster mode. If we set spark.driver.host property, Spark will create Actor on the hostname or ip as setted, which will leads an error.&lt;br/&gt;
So we should ignore this config item in yarn-cluster mode.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=joshrosen&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;joshrosen&quot;&gt;joshrosen&lt;/a&gt;] pointed, we also ignore it in standalone cluster mode.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
